# Overnight operating system (Desktop v1)

Authority: [docs/overnight-runs/CONTROL.json](../docs/overnight-runs/CONTROL.json)

## Session start (mandatory)

1. Read `docs/overnight-runs/CONTROL.json`.
2. Verify `canonical.sha` against `git rev-parse HEAD` on the Lead worktree.
3. `git fetch origin` and verify `canonical.remote_sha` matches `origin/overnight/lead-integration`.
4. Do not trust chat history over CONTROL.json + git state.

## Stage model

- A **stage** is one small integration unit (30–90 minutes), not necessarily one backlog item.
- **Lead-direct implementation** is the default.
- Use **one active write lane** by default; use two only for clearly separate file paths.
- **Subagents** are for bounded research or inventory only — not persistent implementation workers.
- Produce a **first saved deliverable within 15 minutes** of branch creation.
- Do **not** stop merely because a stage finished; after integration PASS, select the next `READY_*` package immediately.

## Lanes and branches

| Role | Worktree | Branch |
|------|----------|--------|
| Lead | `127-si-shooting-challenge` | `overnight/lead-integration` |
| Worker | `127-si-worktrees/worker-{a-d}` | `overnight/v2-run/worker-[a-d]-s[stage]-[scope]` |

Before every `git commit` or Lead merge commit:

```bash
python tools/overnight/assert_git_lane.py --role lead
# or
python tools/overnight/assert_git_lane.py --role worker --lane worker-a
```

## Integration

1. Write stage auth doc from `docs/overnight-runs/stages/_TEMPLATE-AUTHORIZED.md`.
2. Implement on worker branch (or Lead-direct in worker worktree).
3. Merge to Lead in documented order.
4. Run regression: Lambda 66, offline 97, targeted carry-forward.
5. Update CONTROL.json queue states and canonical SHA.
6. Update `docs/overnight-runs/results/UNATTENDED-RUN-STATUS.md` at **milestones only**.

## Status log milestones

Log only: stage authorized, first deliverable, package committed, integration started, tests completed, Lead pushed, run blocked, run stopped.

## Pending approvals

Record blocked commands in `CONTROL.json` → `pending_approvals`. Continue independent READY work when possible. Never use destructive workarounds.

## Hard blocks (require explicit Mike authorization)

- PROD deployment or PROD automation changes
- Credentials or environment-variable changes
- Archive / historical base modification
- Real parent/athlete communications or external sends
- Paid / real-user external activations (Make prod, Fillout prod, AWS affecting live traffic, etc.)
- `git reset --hard`, `git clean`, force push, branch/file deletion (unless Mike explicitly authorizes)
- Package installation, AWS account changes outside an authorized package
- Tutorials table changes (C-026) until unblocked
- Learning Activities Airtable implementation (C-009) until owner schema approval

**DEV schema under an authorized feature package:** creating, renaming, replacing, or deleting **DEV-only** fields/views/fixtures for the current approved overnight feature is **allowed** (Lead-direct) per [DEV-EXECUTION-AND-PROMOTION-MODEL.md](../docs/development/DEV-EXECUTION-AND-PROMOTION-MODEL.md). Do not park routine DEV field work in `pending_approvals`. Still stop for PROD, archive, and high-risk triggers.

## Cloud Agents

Cloud Agents have **no integration authority**. Desktop Lead merges to `overnight/lead-integration` only. Cloud phase is out of scope until Desktop v1 trial passes.

## Approval profile

Initial profile: **Balanced** — see [docs/overnight-runs/APPROVAL-PROFILE.md](../docs/overnight-runs/APPROVAL-PROFILE.md).

Manual Cursor setting required: **Cursor Settings → Agents → Approvals & Execution → Run Mode → Auto-review**.
